<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `subject` String field on the `x_[scope]_case` custom table
    inside the scoped application `x_[scope]`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (Data-Model Mapping verbatim):
        Field    Type           Constraints
        subject  String(255)    Mandatory

    Per AAP Section 0.4.4 the case-submission portal page populates this field
    as one of the five user-supplied inputs (subject, type, description,
    requester_name, requester_email). Per AAP Section 0.7.4 this field is one
    of EXACTLY THREE columns whitelisted by the portal status-lookup endpoint
    for return to anonymous callers - "the lookup page returns ONLY status,
    subject, opened_date - no internal fields exposed". Therefore `subject` is
    the primary human-readable label of a case across BOTH the internal user
    surface (list/form views, dashboards, related lists) AND the external
    requester surface (submission confirmation, status-lookup response).

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java line 137-139:
            @Column(name = "cm_case_title")
            @Size(min = 1)
            private String title;
        ArkCase's `title` was a JPA String column on `acm_case_file` mapped
        to physical column `cm_case_title`, with Bean Validation
        `@Size(min = 1)` enforcing a non-empty value at the JSR-380
        validator layer (effectively a NOT-NULL-AND-NOT-EMPTY check). The
        ServiceNow target replaces both the @Column declaration AND the
        @Size constraint with this single dictionary entry: `mandatory=true`
        is the platform-native equivalent of `@Size(min=1)`, and the
        `<max_length>255</max_length>` ceiling caps overlong values without
        a custom validator. The platform enforces mandatory on every insert
        / update through the standard form, the Table API, the scripted
        REST submission endpoint, and any seed scripts.
      - The field name is `subject` (lowercase, 7 chars; NOT `title`,
        NOT `case_title`, NOT `caseTitle`) per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim.
        This is an INTENTIONAL rename from ArkCase: AAP Section 0.5.1
        explicitly renames `title` -> `subject` so the case table aligns
        with the conventional ServiceNow "subject" field naming pattern
        (incident.short_description / cmdb_ci.short_description carry the
        equivalent semantic in OOB tables, and the platform's email-driven
        intake patterns universally name the human-readable summary
        column `subject`). The rename also mirrors the sibling
        `x_[scope]_case_task.subject` field (AAP Section 0.5.7's
        x_[scope]_case_task table) - both case and case_task tables thus
        carry identically-named human-readable summary columns, easing
        cross-table list views, reports, and portal widget templates.
      - ArkCase's `acm_case_file.cm_case_title` had no explicit length
        cap in the JPA annotations (defaulting to the database-engine
        VARCHAR(255) for MySQL InnoDB). AAP Section 0.5.7 codifies that
        de-facto cap as the explicit `String(255)` constraint here.

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1, 0.7.2, 0.7.4):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to `x_[scope]_case`
        within the scoped application, and `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>`
        bind THIS dictionary record to the same scope by `source` attribute
        lookup. NO global-scope writes - the OOB tables `task`, `incident`,
        `sys_user`, etc. are never modified.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` text-node values resolve by scope source name
        (`x_[scope]`), not by literal sys_id. The `<sys_id>`
        text-node value is THIS record's own deterministic primary key
        (MD5 of the canonical field identifier `x_[scope]_case.subject`)
        and is NOT a reference to any other record. The MD5 derivation
        guarantees that re-generation of this Update Set on any agent run
        produces a byte-identical `<sys_id>` (no random UUIDs), which is
        required for clean Update-Set re-import on a fresh PDI without
        creating duplicate sys_dictionary rows.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP convention;
        the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio
        creation time. The placeholder appears in `<name>`, `<sys_scope>`,
        `<sys_package>`, and `<sys_update_name>` consistently.
      - mandatory=true at the dictionary level (AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim:
        "subject | String(255) | Mandatory"; matches AAP Section 0.4.4's
        portal-submission requirement that `subject` be one of the five
        user-supplied inputs - a portal submission with an empty subject
        is invalid and MUST fail at the platform-validation layer before
        the scripted REST endpoint's GlideRecord.insert() ever fires).
        This also matches the source-side @Size(min=1) constraint on
        ArkCase's `title` field semantically (an empty string is rejected).
      - read_only=false: internal users with the case_manager role (and
        case_agent role on assigned cases per AAP Section 0.5.6 ACL
        matrix) may correct an erroneous subject AFTER the case is
        created. Internal-user write authorization is governed by the
        table-level ACLs in ../acl/ - this dictionary entry deliberately
        does NOT carry per-role write_roles since the table-level ACLs
        apply uniformly across all editable fields.
      - default_value is EMPTY (no implicit default) per AAP Section 0.5.7
        and the agent prompt's Phase 4 verbatim. Subject is the most
        important user-facing identifier of a case; defaulting silently
        to a placeholder string ("Untitled Case", "(no subject)", etc.)
        would silently mask submissions that failed mandatory enforcement
        and pollute the Manager View dashboard's case-by-status / case-
        by-type / case-by-priority reports with semantically-empty rows.
      - audit=false per AAP Section 0.3.1 minimal-change clause and the
        agent prompt's Phase 4. The status field on this same table
        carries audit=true because every state transition must be
        reconstructable post-hoc; subject is descriptive metadata, not a
        regulated lifecycle attribute, so the additional sys_audit row
        per update is unnecessary overhead for a POC.
      - max_length=255 EXACTLY per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. NOT 4000
        (description, the long-form free-text body), NOT 100
        (requester_name / requester_email, the short identity strings),
        NOT 40 (number / type / status / priority, the controlled-
        vocabulary identifier-style strings). 255 is the largest defined
        ceiling on a free-form String column for this scoped table and
        accommodates a meaningful summary phrase without bleeding into
        long-form description territory.
      - choice=0 = "Free-form String, no choice list" (NOT 3 like the
        type / status / priority fields). Subject is unconstrained
        natural-language text; constraining it to a choice list would
        defeat its purpose as a per-case unique human-readable label.
      - unique=false: multiple cases with the same subject are explicitly
        permitted (e.g., a recurring "Quarterly Compliance Review" case
        can recur each fiscal quarter without colliding). Uniqueness
        enforcement at the case level is delegated entirely to the
        auto-generated `number` field per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim
        (which carries unique=true on its own dictionary row in
        ./x_[scope]_case_number.xml).
      - text_index=true future-proofs basic full-text search across the
        case list / dashboards. Subject is the highest-cardinality
        free-form String on x_[scope]_case (description is also free-
        form but is text/varchar-large with different indexing
        semantics). Internal users searching the case list by partial
        subject phrase (the most common search pattern in OOB ServiceNow
        list filters) benefit directly from the index; the cost is
        negligible at POC data volumes.
      - spell_check=true is appropriate for a human-readable label that
        users type freely. The platform surfaces inline spell-check
        suggestions on the form input, improving UX without affecting
        persistence.
      - No reference target: this is a free-form String field, not a
        Reference field. All `<reference*>` elements are empty and
        `<table_reference>false</table_reference>`.
      - No PII: while the field stores synthetic case-summary phrases
        in the demo seed data, NO real names, real email addresses,
        real phone numbers, real organization names, or real case
        content from the source ArkCase database are placed in this
        column at any point in the build (per AAP Section 0.3.2
        synthetic-data-only constraint). Demo seed values are
        fabricated phrases such as "General inquiry about benefits"
        or "Complaint regarding service delay".

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER `../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml`
        (parent table), since `<name>x_[scope]_case</name>` references
        the table by name.
      - This record MUST load BEFORE the consumers that read or write
        the `subject` column:
          * ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_submit.xml
            (the scripted REST submission endpoint - writes this field
            from the user's portal-form input on every anonymous case
            submission; AAP Section 0.4.4 lists `subject` as one of
            the five user-supplied inputs the page collects)
          * ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_status_lookup.xml
            (the scripted REST status-lookup endpoint - returns this
            field as one of EXACTLY THREE whitelisted output fields
            per AAP Section 0.7.4: "the lookup page returns ONLY
            status, subject, opened_date". The lookup endpoint MUST
            include this field in its response payload for valid
            number queries and MUST NOT include any other case
            field beyond status, subject, and opened_date)
          * ../portal/widgets/sp_widget_x_[scope]_case_submission_widget.xml
            (the submission widget binds its subject input to this
            field via the scripted REST endpoint above)
          * ../portal/widgets/sp_widget_x_[scope]_case_lookup_widget.xml
            (the lookup widget renders this field from the status-
            lookup endpoint's response payload)
          * ../portal/widgets/sp_widget_x_[scope]_case_confirmation_widget.xml
            (the confirmation widget echoes back the submitted subject
            alongside the auto-generated case number)
          * ../script_includes/x_[scope]_CasePortalService.xml
            (the submitCase() and lookupCase() helper methods read /
            write this field on behalf of the scripted REST endpoints)
          * ../reports/x_[scope]_my_open_cases.xml (list-style report
            includes subject as a visible column for at-a-glance
            recognition of each open case row)
          * ../reports/x_[scope]_my_overdue_tasks.xml (when joined to
            the case via case_task.case, the parent case subject is a
            visible column for at-a-glance recognition of which case
            an overdue task belongs to)
          * ../seed-data/cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_*.xml (synthetic
            demo cases that MUST populate this mandatory field with
            realistic non-PII summary phrases to satisfy AAP Section
            0.7.4 minimum-data threshold of "at least 10 cases across
            all statuses, both case types represented")
-->
<record_update table="sys_dictionary">
